The [https://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Operating system operating system (OS)] is the main software system on your computer running all the programs that you want to run.

OpenTTD currently runs in the following operating systems:
* AmigaOS <strong>[*]</strong> [http://www.os4depot.net/index.php?function=showfile&file=game/strategy/openttd.lha]
* BeOS 5, Zeta 1.1 (x86 only) [http://bebits.com/app/3810]
* FreeBSD
* Linux [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717] (NOTE: different Linux variations and distributions behave differently, but some of them include OpenTTD in their packaging system in up-to-date version)
* Maemo <strong>[*]</strong> [http://openttd.toimii.net/maemo/]
* MacOS X (10.2 or newer) [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]
* MorphOS [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]
* NetBSD
* OS/2 [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]
* Palm OS 5 <strong>[*]</strong> [http://www.esoftinteractive.com/openttd.html]
* Pocket PC <strong>[*]</strong> [http://www.esoftinteractive.com/openttd.html]
* PSP <strong>[*]</strong> [http://openttd.teamjak.net/]
* SkyOS <strong>[*]</strong>
* Windows 95/98/ME/2000/NT/XP/VISTA [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]
* Zaurus PDA <strong>[*]</strong> [http://zsi2.stonekeep.com/index.php?v=d&a=2127]

<strong>[*]</strong> Currently not an official port. This version is not maintained by OpenTTD developers.

Additionally, OpenTTD is known to run under [http://www.reactos.com/ ReactOS], and GP2X[http://wiki.gp2x.org/wiki/OpenTTD]


Success has also been reported for the following system(s):
* (0.4.0.1) Solaris 9/04 on a SUN Ultra-2 dual 170MHz UltraSparc-I with a Creator 2D Graphics Adapter.